Package: node-execa
Version: 0.10.0+dfsg-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Javascript Maintainers <pkg-javascript-devel@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 28
Depends: nodejs, node-cross-spawn, node-get-stream (>= 3.0.0), node-is-stream (>= 1.1.0), node-npm-run-path (>= 2.0.0), node-p-finally (>= 1.0.0), node-signal-exit (>= 3.0.0), node-strip-eof (>= 1.0.0)
Section: javascript
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/sindresorhus/execa#readme
Description: better `child_process`
 This is better in the following ways:
  - Promise interface.
  - Strips EOF from the output so you don't have to `stdout.trim()`.
  - Supports shebang binaries cross-platform.
  - Improved Windows support.
  - Higher max buffer. 10 MB instead of 200 KB.
  - Executes locally installed binaries by name.
  - Cleans up spawned processes when the parent process dies.
 .
 Node.js is an event-based server-side JavaScript engine.
